spirit:component.spirit:description: The Triple Modular Redundancy (TMR) Voter, used at the boundary of a TMR subsystem to output a single voted bus interface from the three input interfaces. The core can be configured to vote many bus interfaces, including LMB, BRAM, AXI4, AXI4-Lite, AXI4-Stream, INTERRUPT, IOBUS, UART, GPIO, and IIC. It also provides generic discrete signal voting, which can also be used for other bus interfaces. The voter also supports a lockstep mode, for easier connection of slave bus interfaces. It is highly recommended to use block automation in Vivado IP Integrator to create TMR subsystems. To do this, instantiate a TMR Manager in the hierarchical sub-block to be triplicated.
